    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-07-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="389" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d389">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wharton</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Ryan</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-07-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 29,
                            1890</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Ryan is informed that his telegram of the 24th was not deciphered until
                        yesterday. Mr. Mizner had been telegraphed to on the 20th, instructing him
                        to tender impartial good offices, but no reply has been received from him.
                        Action upon Mexican proposition must be delayed until Mr. Mizner can be
                        reached. Ask if Mexico is in telegraphic communication with her legation in
                        Guatemala.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
